content: My problem with P&R is not so much the bugs. I’ve played it for some 60+ hours and I’ve not really seen much of those. But then the lack or scarcity of information is so much. Like I’m subsidizing an industry and I have no idea how much the cost of running that industry is so that I know how much subsidy is enough or too much. Then, there are no graphs to monitor in more details how an industry is playing out so that you can see how your subsidy is helping. There are so many cases like this where it feels like you’re just making policies in a vacuum and can’t follow up on them better. Also there is no clarity about how and when GDP is calculated and all that. I think they try to make it like in real life but in game, that leads to estimates that go up and down and seem random throughout the year which some people would consider as a bug. I wish there was more communication about how things run.

referenced_message.content: I think P&R would be great in this if it wasn't buggy. It does have a lot of depth but 80% is not working properly or at all. Also the Distant Worlds series has a nice mechanic where you can choose what parts of the game you want to delegate to the CPU and what parts you want to handle yourself.
